Load data

Load the results from each analysis

oxygenGenes <- read_csv(here("data/oxygenGenes.csv.gz"))
oxygenTranscripts <- read_csv(here("data/oxygenTranscripts.csv.gz"))
oxygenDTU <- read_csv(here("data/oxygenDTU.csv.gz"))

Supp table 1 - Highest expressed transcripts

top_expressed <- oxygenTranscripts %>%
  dplyr::arrange(desc(logCPM)) %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene" = "GeneName",
                "Transcript" = "TranscriptName", 
                "Transcript Biotype" = "Transcript_biotype",
                "Transcript Length" = "length",
                "logCPM") 

top_expressed$logCPM <- format(
  round(as.numeric(top_expressed$logCPM), 2),
  nsmall = 2)

top_expressed %>%
  DT::datatable()
## Warning in instance$preRenderHook(instance): It seems your data is too big for
## client-side DataTables. You may consider server-side processing:
## https://rstudio.github.io/DT/server.html

Save table

writexl::write_xlsx(top_expressed, here("tables/supp_table1.xlsx"))

Supp table 2 - triple overlap genes

sig_genes <- oxygenGenes %>%
  dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05 & abs(logFC) > 1) %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene",
                "GeneName",
                "DGE logFC" = "logFC",
                "DGE FDR" = "FDR") %>%
  mutate("DGE FDR" = formatC(`DGE FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "DGE logFC" = format(round(`DGE logFC`, 2), nsmall = 2))

sig_tx <- oxygenTranscripts %>%
  dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05 & abs(logFC) > 1) %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene",
                "Transcript",
                "TranscriptName",
                "DTE logFC" = "logFC",
                "DTE FDR" = "FDR") %>%
  mutate("DTE FDR" = formatC(`DTE FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "DTE logFC" = format(round(`DTE logFC`, 2), nsmall = 2))

sig_dtu <- oxygenDTU %>%
  dplyr::filter(geneFDR < 0.05) %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene",
                "gene_name",
                "DTU FDR" = "geneFDR") %>%
  mutate("DTU FDR" = formatC(`DTU FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"))

triple_overlap <- sig_tx %>%
  inner_join(sig_genes,
            by = "Gene") %>%
  inner_join(sig_dtu,
            by = "Gene") %>%
  distinct() %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene ID" = "Gene",
                "Gene Name" = "gene_name",
                "DGE logFC",
                "DGE FDR",
                "Transcript ID" = "Transcript",
                "Transcript Name" = "TranscriptName",
                "DTE logFC",
                "DTE FDR",
                "DTU FDR") %>%
  dplyr::arrange(`DGE FDR`)
## Warning in inner_join(., sig_dtu, by = "Gene"): Detected an unexpected many-to-many relationship between `x` and `y`.
##  Row 12 of `x` matches multiple rows in `y`.
##  Row 163 of `y` matches multiple rows in `x`.
##  If a many-to-many relationship is expected, set `relationship =
##   "many-to-many"` to silence this warning.
triple_overlap %>% DT::datatable()

Save table

writexl::write_xlsx(triple_overlap, here("tables/supp_table2.xlsx"))

Supp table 3 - DTE results

dte <- oxygenTranscripts %>%
  dplyr::select("Transcript ID" = "Transcript",
                "Transcript Name" = "TranscriptName",
                "Gene ID" = "Gene",
                "Gene Name" = "GeneName",
                "logCPM",
                "logFC",
                "FDR") %>%
  dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05 & abs(logFC) > 1) %>%
  mutate("FDR" = formatC(FDR, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "logFC" = format(round(logFC, 2), nsmall = 2),
         "logCPM" = format(round(logCPM, 2), nsmall = 2))

dte %>% DT::datatable()
writexl::write_xlsx(dte, here("tables/supp_table3a.xlsx"))
down_dte <- oxygenTranscripts %>%
  dplyr::select("Transcript ID" = "Transcript",
                "Transcript Name" = "TranscriptName",
                "Gene ID" = "Gene",
                "Gene Name" = "GeneName",
                "logCPM",
                "logFC",
                "FDR") %>%
  dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05 & logFC <= -1) %>%
  mutate("FDR" = formatC(FDR, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "logFC" = format(round(logFC, 2), nsmall = 2),
         "logCPM" = format(round(logCPM, 2), nsmall = 2))

down_dte %>% DT::datatable()
writexl::write_xlsx(down_dte, here("tables/supp_table3b.xlsx"))
up_dte <- oxygenTranscripts %>%
  dplyr::select("Transcript ID" = "Transcript",
                "Transcript Name" = "TranscriptName",
                "Gene ID" = "Gene",
                "Gene Name" = "GeneName",
                "logCPM",
                "logFC",
                "FDR") %>%
  dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05 & logFC >= 1) %>%
  mutate("FDR" = formatC(FDR, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "logFC" = format(round(logFC, 2), nsmall = 2),
         "logCPM" = format(round(logCPM, 2), nsmall = 2))  

up_dte %>% DT::datatable()
writexl::write_xlsx(up_dte, here("tables/supp_table3c.xlsx"))

Supp table 4 - DTU results

dtu_results <- oxygenDTU %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene",
                "Gene Name" = "gene_name",
                "Transcript",
                "Transcript Name" = "transcript_name",
                "Gene FDR" = "geneFDR",
                "Transcript FDR" = "txpFDR") %>%
  mutate(
    "Gene FDR" = formatC(`Gene FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"),
    "Transcript FDR" = formatC(`Transcript FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e")
  )

dtu_results %>% DT::datatable()
## Warning in instance$preRenderHook(instance): It seems your data is too big for
## client-side DataTables. You may consider server-side processing:
## https://rstudio.github.io/DT/server.html
writexl::write_xlsx(dtu_results, here("tables/supp_table4.xlsx"))

Supp table 5 - Gene significant in DTE and DTU

ranked_dtu <- sig_dtu %>%
  distinct() %>%
  mutate(rank_in_dtu = 1:dim(.)[1])

dte_and_dtu <- sig_dtu %>%
  dplyr::filter(Gene %in% sig_tx$Gene,
                !Gene %in% sig_genes$Gene) %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene",
                "gene_name",
                "DTU FDR") %>%
  inner_join(sig_tx %>%
              dplyr::select("Gene",
                            "Transcript",
                            "TranscriptName",
                            "DTE logFC",
                            "DTE FDR"),
            by = "Gene") %>%
  left_join(ranked_dtu %>%
              dplyr::select("Gene", "rank_in_dtu"),
            by = "Gene") %>%
  dplyr::select("Gene" = "gene_name",
                "Transcript" = "TranscriptName",
                "DTU FDR",
                "DTE FDR",
                "DTE logFC",
                "Rank in DTU" = "rank_in_dtu") %>%
  dplyr::arrange(`Rank in DTU`) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  mutate("DTU FDR" = formatC(`DTU FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "DTE FDR" = formatC(`DTE FDR`, digits = 2, format = "e"),
         "DTE logFC" = format(round(as.numeric(`DTE logFC`), 2), nsmall = 2))
## Warning in inner_join(., sig_tx %>% dplyr::select("Gene", "Transcript", : Detected an unexpected many-to-many relationship between `x` and `y`.
##  Row 48 of `x` matches multiple rows in `y`.
##  Row 63 of `y` matches multiple rows in `x`.
##  If a many-to-many relationship is expected, set `relationship =
##   "many-to-many"` to silence this warning.
dte_and_dtu %>% DT::datatable()
writexl::write_xlsx(dte_and_dtu,
                    here("tables/supp_table5.xlsx"))
